{
  "stem": "23428.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, the-- you know, my-- my shedding of religion has really much to do with my intellectual development later.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I think hasn't been final until I was, what, 20, 21, must be 22.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, it's not that I considered myself second-class citizen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In fact, you know, very emphatically we never did, refused to accept that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it's fascist society that treated us like second-class citizens in-- in many simple ways, you know, from not being allowed to go to the theater, having to sit on yellow benches in the parks, ultimately, something we actually never did, wearing a yellow star on our clothes.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But you know, it's obvious that apart from the-- the killing off of Jews in the later course of the war, ever since 1936 Jews were considered [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] second or third-class.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] Just to give you an example, in the parks of Berlin there were signs put up which said, no dogs or Jews, in that order.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So even when you're a 9- or 10-year-old, there was no ambiguity about what that meant to be a Jew in that country.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not one.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, not true.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Budapest.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In Budapest, there were Jewish classmates I had, yes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But these were Hungarians, you see, so German school didn't worry about this.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "As far as they're concerned, they were Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not in Berlin.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was not-- well, you know, not in-- not in grammar school.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Obviously, not in high school, because it was run by the Jesuits.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At the same moment.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well-- [PAUSES FOR 9 SECONDS] well, we reacted it to it, I think, in two ways.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One, being depressed about refusal of that society to accept us as equals.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And another one-- another one was the attitude of never accepting that division.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
